
    THE armed cop left work and went to a block of flats in City Deep, Joburg.But then he got into an argument with two residents and shot them dead.Manuel Mario (35) found himself face to face with the killer cop.He tried to run away but was shot three times by the off-duty constable.His neighbour heard his screams and went to investigate, but was beaten to death with a plank.The cop, who was allegedly mentally ill, injured two other people.When the cops from Moffat View Police Station heard the gunshots last Tuesday, they rushed to help.But the policeman shot at them as well, forcing the cops to retaliate. A shoot-out ensued and the killer cop was shot dead.Now the families of the policeman and his victims want the government to bury all three of them.Rebecca Makhanya (42), Mario’s girlfriend, said they got by on the money he made at his small salon.“He didn’t have regular customers.“Life is difficult now because we don’t have money to bury him.“We don’t want anything fancy – just money for his burial.“We want the police to take full responsibility for this,” said Rebecca.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjstbhKEiu0ASJ3uTlczEDapTQ6WPFCVCypz270nYOTpkOuBSCjH1bG90LFydR5n0b7BVEiFm1wUZPgvNCAMZUM9idaFjYYFMcyW0JTnByuXVxZ1n-096SjcV3DSMnG_UQ_HjLJ2rN122O8bOIIRqpYj2o6epZBY5ZvIzFcBBWwa2MDL04npZKj48miySItVX5jUomTxq-obV9q0h_62WY7V6qQq6bLLwLukMw3zN3aCQkeohWtcZABS_3_HhQ3Zxj1q4BI2DQr7nhXwsfIYLEG8fPlPztTA\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzLei7z68H1rbEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
